{"title": "Bhagavad Gita", "description": "The content of the text is a conversation between Krishna and Arjuna taking place on the battlefield of Kurukshetra just prior to the start of a climactic war. Responding to Arjuna's confusion and moral dilemma, Krishna explains to Arjuna his duties as a warrior and Prince and elaborates on a number of different Yogic and Vedantic philosophies, with examples and analogies. This has led to the Gita often being described as a concise guide to Hindu philosophy and also as a practical, self-contained guide to life. During the discourse, Krishna reveals his identity as the Supreme Being Himself (Bhagavan), blessing Arjuna with an awe-inspiring glimpse of His divine absolute form. (Wikipedia)", "duration": 10493, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "221", "name": " Unknown"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt/Bhagavad_Gita_1003.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Other religions"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Chris Masterson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lizzie Driver"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [1392], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/bhagavad_gita_0803_librivox/bhagavadgita_00_64kb.mp3", "duration": 183}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1: Of the Distress of Arjuna", "readers": [1392], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/bhagavad_gita_0803_librivox/bhagavadgita_01_64kb.mp3", "duration": 580}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2: Of Doctrines", "readers": [174], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/bhagavad_gita_0803_librivox/bhagavadgita_02_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1076}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 3: Virtue in Work", "readers": [2068], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/bhagavad_gita_0803_librivox/bhagavadgita_03_64kb.mp3", "duration": 539}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 4: Of the Religion of Knowledge", "readers"